<text>Ealhmund is an Anglo-Saxon male name. Notable people with the name include:

* Saint Alchmund of Hexham (died 780 or 781)
* King Ealhmund of Kent (ruled in 784)
* Saint Alchmund of Derby (died 800)
* Bishop Ealhmund of Winchester (died between 805 and 814)</text><links>
